In Hong Kong, a two-year-old boy recovered from bird flu, while a three-year-old boy and a man died from the H5N1 strain.
A 13-year-old girl is currently hospitalized.
Hospitals in Hong Kong are testing all patients for the flu, including relatives showing symptoms.
Macao reassures residents that imported poultry is safe.
Hong Kong and Guangdong are coordinating efforts to monitor and prevent the spread of the virus.
Hong Kong's Department of Health is actively managing the situation, with nine confirmed cases and four deaths.
Shenzhen has not reported any cases, ensuring the safety of poultry consumption.
